        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(imessage): native poll support — create, read, vote",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nOpenClaw's iMessage channel could not complete the native Messages poll loop. Agents could not create or vote on polls, and received polls reached the model as an empty balloon placeholder.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\niOS/macOS 26 and the `imsg` bridge support native poll create, decode, and vote operations. This change keeps that behavior in the iMessage plugin while extending the generic channel action contract only where core needs a canonical delivery route for safe authorization and one-turn narration suppression.\n\n- Create native polls through the existing portable `poll` action.\n- Render inbound questions, options, and tallies.\n- Vote by exactly one option index, label, or UUID.\n- Gate create on `pollPayloadMessage`; gate voting on both `pollVoteMessage` and `poll.vote`.\n- Refresh capabilities before rejecting an action, covering bridge upgrades without a gateway restart.\n- Resolve iMessage target aliases to one canonical route, reject conflicting aliases, and apply the existing cross-context action guard.\n- Suppress only the first exact same-provider/account/route narration of the selected option for 30 seconds.\n\nThe required bridge contract landed in [openclaw/imsg#148](https://github.com/openclaw/imsg/pull/148).\n\n## User Impact\n\n- Agents on iOS/macOS 26+ can create, read, and vote on native Messages polls.\n- Received polls are readable instead of appearing empty.\n- Unsupported or stale `imsg` installations fail with an actionable upgrade/relaunch/status-probe message.\n- A vote no longer produces a redundant one-word text beside the native vote; unrelated chats/accounts remain unaffected.\n- No new configuration is required. Existing `channels.imessage.actions.polls: false` remains the opt-out.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- Focused iMessage Vitest: 76 passed across actions, discovery, rendering, and status probing.\n- Generic routing/policy Vitest: 78 passed; targeted message-tool suppression passed in both Vitest projects.\n- Docs MDX, `git diff --check`, touched-file formatting, and oxlint passed.\n- Full changed-lane Testbox: `tbx_01kweafa9vnfbhv3s8fzqvahh0` — repository guards, project typecheck, core/extensions/scripts oxlint, and import-cycle checks passed ([run](https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/actions/runs/28502152875)).\n- Fresh independent Codex autoreview: clean after all accepted findings were fixed.\n- Real macOS 26.4.1 gateway → message tool → iMessage → `imsg` proof: inbound poll rendered; native associated vote row type 4000 recorded with `delivered=1`, `err=0`; duplicate narration suppressed while a matching send to another route remained visible.\n- Maintainer macOS 26.5.2 selector/runtime probe passed. Local native injection was blocked by SIP, so native delivery evidence uses the contributor's real-device run plus the independently landed `imsg` contract proof.\n",
        "branch": "feat/imessage-poll-action",
